quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  39,32,"Who is worse than one who utters a lie against Allah, and denies the truth when it comes to him? Is there not an abode in hell for the disbelievers"
  39,33,And the one who brings the truth and believes in it - they are those who are the pious people
  39,34,They shall have all that they will desire from their Lord. That is the reward of the righteous people
  39,35,Allah will expiate their evil deeds from them and give them the reward according to their best deeds
  39,36,"Is Allah not sufficient for His servants? Yet they try to frighten you with those besides Him! The one whom Allah sends astray, there is no guide for him"
  39,37,"And the one whom Allah guides, there is none to mislead him. Is not Allah the Mighty, the Possessor of Retribution"
  39,38,"And surely, if you ask them: “Who created the heavens and the earth?” Surely, they will say: “Allah.” Say: “Do you see the things that you invoke besides Allah, if Allah intends some harm for me, could they remove His harm, or if He intends some Mercy for me, could they withhold His Mercy?\" Say: “Allah is sufficient for me. Those who trust in Him, must put their trust.”"
  39,39,"Say: (O Muhammad): “O my people! Work according to your way, surely I am working (according to my way). Then you will come to know"
  39,40,"to whom a disgracing punishment will come, and on whom an everlasting punishment will descend.”"